info.description:
androidtv-smart-tv-app.clarobrasil.mobi

O11 – Scripts Overview

This collection includes a folder “O11 – Provider Scripts” with four requests that demonstrate how to invoke O11 provider scripts using environment variables for easy configuration:

- Manifest script (GET): returns playback URLs and DRM metadata given a content id.
- CDM script (POST): takes a DRM challenge + PSSH and returns a signed license or license URL/headers.
- Events script (GET): pings/heartbeats for player analytics and service liveness.
- Channels script (GET): returns an available channel list for a provider.

Common query/body parameters
- action: one of manifest | cdm | events | channels
- bind: client binding key
- proxy: optional proxy setting
- doh/dns: DNS resolution strategy
- worker: execution profile
- id: content/channel identifier (manifest/channels)
- drm: DRM provider or scheme (manifest/cdm)
- pssh, challenge: CDM-only inputs
- heartbeaturl, heartbeatparams: Events-only inputs

Example response – Manifest (JSON)
```
{
  "ok": true,
  "id": "{{id}}",
  "streams": [
    { "type": "dash", "url": "https://cdn.example.com/manifest.mpd", "drm": {"scheme": "widevine", "pssh": "..."} }
  ],
  "headers": {"User-Agent": "O11-Agent/1.0"}
}
```

Example response – CDM (JSON)
```
{
  "ok": true,
  "licenseUrl": "https://license.example.com/widevine",
  "headers": {"X-Custom": "abc"},
  "license": "<base64 or binary payload if inlined>"
}
```

How to use
1) Set environment variables (Dev env already present): o11_base_url, providerId, bind, proxy, doh, dns, worker, id, drm, pssh, challenge, heartbeaturl, heartbeatparams.
2) Open any request under the folder and Send. Tweak params in Params/Body as needed.
3) Use the examples above to parse responses.

See folder: O11 – Provider Scripts for detailed, per-script descriptions.
